WEBVTT

00:00:00.000 --> 00:00:16.580
Alhamdulillah, Rabbul Aalamin, Ar-Rahman, Ar-Raheem, Maliki, Yawm, Al-Deen, Iyaka, Na'bud, Wa-Iyaka, Nasta'i'een,

00:00:16.580 --> 00:00:26.140
Ehdina, Sirata, Al-Mustaqeem, Sirata, Al-Ladin, Al-Aamta, Alayhim, Ghayri, Al-Mawdhub, Alayhim,

00:00:26.140 --> 00:00:35.960
Bismillah, Ar-Rahman, Ar-Raheem, Alhamdulillah, Rabbul Aalamin,

00:00:35.960 --> 00:00:53.960
We praise Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala, we send blessings and salutations upon the Masterpiece Muhammad, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam,

00:00:53.960 --> 00:01:01.560
his entire household and all his companions, may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless them all and may he bless every single one of us.

00:01:01.560 --> 00:01:10.560
My beloved brothers and sisters in Islam, as you know, the second Taraweeh has just been read and we have entered into the second day of Ramadan.

00:01:10.560 --> 00:01:15.560
And before we know it, believe me, the entire month will have come to an end.

00:01:15.560 --> 00:01:22.560
Every year, the Ramadan passes quicker than the previous year and that is the prophecy of Muhammad, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:01:22.560 --> 00:01:31.560
So just hold in, don't be lazy because Shaytan comes to us and he tends to whisper in our ears and we become lazy after that.

00:01:31.560 --> 00:01:39.560
So after we have had a good start, we tend to become more slack and after that we regret at the end of the month thinking to ourselves,

00:01:39.560 --> 00:01:43.560
why didn't we do this and do that? It was only but a month.

00:01:43.560 --> 00:01:45.560
We ask Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to bless us.

00:01:45.560 --> 00:01:56.560
As promised yesterday, we look at the darkness surrounding the Arabian Peninsula just before the birth of Muhammad, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam.

00:01:56.560 --> 00:02:01.560
In fact, the darkness that the whole globe was upon.

00:02:01.560 --> 00:02:06.560
If you take a look at in India, how a woman was treated,

00:02:06.560 --> 00:02:12.560
she was such that if her husband died, there was no chance of marrying again.

00:02:12.560 --> 00:02:16.560
Most of them burned themselves to death because they were taught that.

00:02:16.560 --> 00:02:23.560
They were brainwashed to believe that that was their system and they believed in reincarnation.

00:02:23.560 --> 00:02:32.560
When a person dies up to today, there are some who believe that the person reappears in the form of some either bird or snake,

00:02:32.560 --> 00:02:35.560
depending on whether they led a good life or a bad one.

00:02:35.560 --> 00:02:39.560
I remember one of the sisters once in my own community telling me

00:02:39.560 --> 00:02:44.560
that they had some people visiting them after the death of one of the relatives

00:02:44.560 --> 00:02:50.560
and as they walked out, they saw a dove sitting on one of the branches of a tree

00:02:50.560 --> 00:02:54.560
and they looked at this dove and they said, oh, that must be this person.

00:02:54.560 --> 00:03:00.560
And when I was told, I thought to myself, well, this dove was alive well before the death of this person.

00:03:00.560 --> 00:03:06.560
But look at how the people's minds are, the darkness at the time of Muhammad, sallallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:03:07.560 --> 00:03:11.560
or just prior to his time, if you take a look at the Arabian Peninsula,

00:03:11.560 --> 00:03:15.560
religiously, as we mentioned yesterday, they worshiped idols,

00:03:15.560 --> 00:03:19.560
so much so that they made idols out of stones

00:03:19.560 --> 00:03:26.560
and when they found a better stone, they would throw away what they used to worship for so many years.

00:03:26.560 --> 00:03:30.560
And when they had a big problem, they would go to someone who had a bigger stone to say,

00:03:30.560 --> 00:03:34.560
hang on, can I borrow your God because I've got an issue, big problem.

00:03:35.560 --> 00:03:40.560
Allahu Akbar, imagine the brains of the people and Umar ibn Al-Khattab radi Allahu Anhu,

00:03:40.560 --> 00:03:46.560
he actually says, as intelligent as he was, he says, we made a God out of dates

00:03:46.560 --> 00:03:49.560
and you know, we could shape it up much more easily than stone.

00:03:49.560 --> 00:03:53.560
So we shaped it up and it was so nice and one day I was very hungry,

00:03:53.560 --> 00:03:56.560
asking the God for food, food, no food came, I ate the God.

00:03:56.560 --> 00:03:59.560
Allahu Akbar, ate the God.

00:03:59.560 --> 00:04:02.560
So this was the type of mentality around the darkness.

00:04:02.560 --> 00:04:05.560
They believed in lots of superstition, as we mentioned last night.

00:04:05.560 --> 00:04:10.560
See something and they believed, oh, this means that will happen and that means this will happen.

00:04:10.560 --> 00:04:13.560
And if this happens, then this. If you see a cinnamon, then that.

00:04:13.560 --> 00:04:17.560
If someone is having hiccups, then another person is remembering them.

00:04:17.560 --> 00:04:20.560
If you sneeze once, that means someone has remembered you and so on.

00:04:20.560 --> 00:04:25.560
This had all come from that particular time and it seeped through across the globe.

00:04:25.560 --> 00:04:31.560
For your information, to this day, some of us are guilty of believing in some of these superstitious items.

00:04:31.560 --> 00:04:36.560
So thereafter, if you look at one of their habits, they visited the fortune tellers.

00:04:36.560 --> 00:04:40.560
Anything happened, they went to the fortune teller and they let him solve their matter.

00:04:40.560 --> 00:04:43.560
And these fortune tellers, they were powerful in the sense that

00:04:43.560 --> 00:04:48.560
they knew how to study the lives of people and they had contact with the spirits.

00:04:48.560 --> 00:04:55.560
As I mentioned yesterday, contact with the spirits, contact with the jinn is not impossible, but it is prohibited.

00:04:55.560 --> 00:04:59.560
We are not allowed to deal in that and we are not allowed to go into that.

00:04:59.560 --> 00:05:04.560
Although we would know how it operates and how to protect ourselves from it,

00:05:04.560 --> 00:05:10.560
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us the ability to recite the verses of the Quran that are relevant.

00:05:10.560 --> 00:05:15.560
We recited them this evening, Ayatul Kursi, as well as the last few verses of Surah Baqarah,

00:05:15.560 --> 00:05:20.560
the most powerful of them, and the last two Surahs of the Quran.

00:05:20.560 --> 00:05:23.560
These are powerful Surahs which should be read every morning and evening

00:05:23.560 --> 00:05:26.560
with the intention of dua and protection.

00:05:27.560 --> 00:05:30.560
And then you find one of the habits they had.

00:05:30.560 --> 00:05:33.560
They did not believe in the life after death.

00:05:33.560 --> 00:05:35.560
They would say,

00:05:40.560 --> 00:05:45.560
Who is going to give life to these bones after they are

00:05:45.560 --> 00:05:49.560
decomposed completely and like dust they become?

00:05:49.560 --> 00:05:50.560
And Allah says,

00:05:57.560 --> 00:06:03.560
Say, He will give those bones life

00:06:03.560 --> 00:06:06.560
who gave them the life in the first place.

00:06:06.560 --> 00:06:10.560
So for Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala to create man in the first place,

00:06:10.560 --> 00:06:12.560
to resurrect him is even easier.

00:06:12.560 --> 00:06:17.560
If you have no BMW and you were to make one,

00:06:17.560 --> 00:06:23.560
you are far more a genius than a person who has just panel-beated a damaged BMW.

00:06:23.560 --> 00:06:24.560
Simple, logic.

00:06:26.560 --> 00:06:29.560
And Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a deeper understanding.

00:06:29.560 --> 00:06:30.560
Obviously,

00:06:31.560 --> 00:06:34.560
Allah has a far higher example than that which we just gave,

00:06:34.560 --> 00:06:37.560
but this was only to bring it closer to our brains and minds.

00:06:37.560 --> 00:06:40.560
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala makes mention of how

00:06:40.560 --> 00:06:43.560
when they were in difficulty, they left their gods.

00:06:43.560 --> 00:06:46.560
They called out to the one deity who created them.

00:06:46.560 --> 00:06:48.560
Whoever made me, I'm calling out to him.

00:06:48.560 --> 00:06:50.560
That was when? When they had a problem.

00:06:50.560 --> 00:06:52.560
When they had difficulties.

00:06:52.560 --> 00:06:53.560
So like Allah says,

00:06:56.560 --> 00:07:07.560
...

00:07:07.560 --> 00:07:10.560
When they were on the ship and when the boat rocks a little bit,

00:07:10.560 --> 00:07:14.560
you know when you're at sea, they would call out to Allah alone.

00:07:14.560 --> 00:07:16.560
And as soon as they come back, what would happen?

00:07:16.560 --> 00:07:20.560
They would immediately start engaging in their polytheism once again,

00:07:20.560 --> 00:07:24.560
worshipping the other false deities besides Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:07:25.560 --> 00:07:28.560
As for the politics, at that particular time,

00:07:28.560 --> 00:07:31.560
people were divided into two major groups.

00:07:31.560 --> 00:07:33.560
You find the people of the Badiyah,

00:07:33.560 --> 00:07:36.560
the people of the desert and the people of the cities.

00:07:36.560 --> 00:07:39.560
And up to today, you find those, mashaAllah,

00:07:39.560 --> 00:07:42.560
who are living in smaller towns have far greater hearts.

00:07:42.560 --> 00:07:46.560
They have far better qualities than those who are in the city,

00:07:46.560 --> 00:07:48.560
who don't even have time to greet you.

00:07:48.560 --> 00:07:51.560
They don't even have time to be hospitable,

00:07:51.560 --> 00:07:54.560
whereas the slow life of those who are further away, mashaAllah,

00:07:54.560 --> 00:07:57.560
one of the secrets why we are here in Polokwani, inshaAllah.

00:07:57.560 --> 00:08:00.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness

00:08:00.560 --> 00:08:02.560
and make our hearts pure at all times.

00:08:02.560 --> 00:08:04.560
Wallahi, it's a point of goodness.

00:08:04.560 --> 00:08:06.560
I feel really that this is about to be,

00:08:06.560 --> 00:08:09.560
if not it has already started as one of the best Ramadans.

00:08:09.560 --> 00:08:13.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not make us from those who lose out.

00:08:13.560 --> 00:08:15.560
Believe me, as I say always,

00:08:15.560 --> 00:08:17.560
it's like a train that is passing.

00:08:17.560 --> 00:08:18.560
You catch it, you catch it.

00:08:18.560 --> 00:08:20.560
You missed it, everybody else caught it.

00:08:20.560 --> 00:08:22.560
You're alone in the station.

00:08:22.560 --> 00:08:25.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala not make us miss our trains and planes.

00:08:25.560 --> 00:08:27.560
I'm sure you know how it feels.

00:08:27.560 --> 00:08:30.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness.

00:08:30.560 --> 00:08:35.560
So they had people in the cities and people out in the deserts,

00:08:35.560 --> 00:08:37.560
in the rural areas so to speak,

00:08:37.560 --> 00:08:41.560
but they had something in common, very strong lineage.

00:08:41.560 --> 00:08:44.560
They were divided into tribes, families,

00:08:44.560 --> 00:08:47.560
and they literally stood up for one another.

00:08:47.560 --> 00:08:49.560
They would fight the other tribe

00:08:49.560 --> 00:08:53.560
because of a problem that it had had with one particular person.

00:08:53.560 --> 00:08:55.560
One camel goes missing, for example,

00:08:55.560 --> 00:08:59.560
and they doubted those people or someone was caught.

00:08:59.560 --> 00:09:01.560
The war lasted 40 years, 40 years.

00:09:01.560 --> 00:09:02.560
People died.

00:09:02.560 --> 00:09:05.560
The next generation did not even know why they were fighting,

00:09:05.560 --> 00:09:06.560
but they continued fighting.

00:09:06.560 --> 00:09:08.560
This was the type of Qabaliya they had.

00:09:08.560 --> 00:09:12.560
They had this tribalism and they had stuck to their clans.

00:09:12.560 --> 00:09:14.560
Sometimes it was used for the good

00:09:14.560 --> 00:09:16.560
and sometimes it was used for the bad.

00:09:16.560 --> 00:09:20.560
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala blessed them by sending them the message.

00:09:20.560 --> 00:09:25.560
But if we take a look at the leadership of these clans

00:09:25.560 --> 00:09:28.560
was always with a certain type of person and family,

00:09:28.560 --> 00:09:33.560
and usually it fell from father to child or to brother and so on,

00:09:33.560 --> 00:09:35.560
and this was the way they led.

00:09:35.560 --> 00:09:37.560
So the leader, the chief, and when he died,

00:09:37.560 --> 00:09:40.560
his son took over or a relative took over,

00:09:40.560 --> 00:09:44.560
but there was something that could raise a person from nothing.

00:09:44.560 --> 00:09:45.560
What was that?

00:09:45.560 --> 00:09:47.560
If someone's level was very low,

00:09:47.560 --> 00:09:50.560
they just had to come up with some poetry,

00:09:50.560 --> 00:09:54.560
which was so powerful linguistically and full of meaning

00:09:54.560 --> 00:09:58.560
that it would instantly raise the rank of that individual

00:09:58.560 --> 00:10:00.560
sometimes to the point of leadership.

00:10:00.560 --> 00:10:01.560
Subhanallah.

00:10:01.560 --> 00:10:02.560
Why?

00:10:02.560 --> 00:10:04.560
They were crazy about eloquence.

00:10:04.560 --> 00:10:05.560
So crazy.

00:10:05.560 --> 00:10:09.560
They were the most powerful people when it came to speech.

00:10:09.560 --> 00:10:11.560
In fact, they were unlettered.

00:10:11.560 --> 00:10:16.560
The bulk of them, almost 100% of them could not read or write,

00:10:16.560 --> 00:10:18.560
but linguistically they were powerful.

00:10:18.560 --> 00:10:21.560
They hardly used slang.

00:10:21.560 --> 00:10:23.560
And Nabi sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:10:23.560 --> 00:10:25.560
as we will see later on,

00:10:25.560 --> 00:10:27.560
as he grew up, he never used slang.

00:10:27.560 --> 00:10:29.560
He was always the most powerful.

00:10:29.560 --> 00:10:34.560
It is reported that he never ever made a linguistic error in his life.

00:10:34.560 --> 00:10:35.560
Subhanallah.

00:10:35.560 --> 00:10:36.560
Nothing.

00:10:36.560 --> 00:10:38.560
That was his gift by Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala.

00:10:38.560 --> 00:10:42.560
And this is why later on we see how they looked at him

00:10:42.560 --> 00:10:44.560
and they listened to him

00:10:44.560 --> 00:10:46.560
and they were mesmerized by what he said.

00:10:46.560 --> 00:10:47.560
Subhanallah.

00:10:47.560 --> 00:10:48.560
Completely shocked.

00:10:48.560 --> 00:10:51.560
So much so that later on the Arabic language

00:10:51.560 --> 00:10:56.560
began to take its rules and correct itself through the Quran.

00:10:56.560 --> 00:10:59.560
Because that was what Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam came with.

00:10:59.560 --> 00:11:03.560
Up to this day, the kuffar, the Christian Arabs

00:11:03.560 --> 00:11:06.560
and those who are non-Muslims from amongst the Arabs,

00:11:06.560 --> 00:11:09.560
they still use the Quran when it comes to linguistics

00:11:09.560 --> 00:11:11.560
in order to correct their language

00:11:11.560 --> 00:11:13.560
and to explain to you what is right and wrong.

00:11:14.560 --> 00:11:15.560
Subhanallah.

00:11:15.560 --> 00:11:17.560
So if you take a look at them

00:11:17.560 --> 00:11:20.560
from the angle of their wealth

00:11:20.560 --> 00:11:22.560
and if you look at them economically,

00:11:22.560 --> 00:11:23.560
what did they have?

00:11:23.560 --> 00:11:25.560
They did not have much in terms of produce

00:11:25.560 --> 00:11:26.560
because it barely rained.

00:11:26.560 --> 00:11:28.560
And if it did, it was all desert.

00:11:28.560 --> 00:11:31.560
But in certain spots, they had had the date palm

00:11:31.560 --> 00:11:33.560
that used to grow a lot.

00:11:33.560 --> 00:11:35.560
And they had a few other things that would grow

00:11:35.560 --> 00:11:36.560
very, very little.

00:11:36.560 --> 00:11:39.560
A lot of their trading happened to be

00:11:39.560 --> 00:11:42.560
with the livestock that they had had.

00:11:42.560 --> 00:11:49.560
They had a lot of camels, donkeys as well as

00:11:49.560 --> 00:11:50.560
goats and sheep.

00:11:50.560 --> 00:11:51.560
Subhanallah.

00:11:51.560 --> 00:11:52.560
The donkeys, obviously,

00:11:52.560 --> 00:11:55.560
they wouldn't really count them as part of livestock as non-edible.

00:11:55.560 --> 00:11:56.560
But at the same time,

00:11:56.560 --> 00:12:00.560
you look at the amount of goats and sheep

00:12:00.560 --> 00:12:01.560
they had had.

00:12:01.560 --> 00:12:02.560
Subhanallah.

00:12:02.560 --> 00:12:03.560
And there was a difference

00:12:03.560 --> 00:12:06.560
between those who had had camels

00:12:06.560 --> 00:12:08.560
and those who had had goats and sheep.

00:12:08.560 --> 00:12:10.560
Those who had had camels up to today,

00:12:10.560 --> 00:12:11.560
those who have camels,

00:12:11.560 --> 00:12:13.560
they have their noses high up in the air.

00:12:13.560 --> 00:12:14.560
We have camels.

00:12:14.560 --> 00:12:16.560
And you know, it's considered very expensive

00:12:16.560 --> 00:12:18.560
and considered something so wealthy.

00:12:18.560 --> 00:12:20.560
Like today, you have someone driving

00:12:20.560 --> 00:12:22.560
the latest motor vehicle.

00:12:22.560 --> 00:12:25.560
There, it was known as the red camel.

00:12:25.560 --> 00:12:27.560
It was something amazing.

00:12:27.560 --> 00:12:30.560
It had value more than the BMWs today.

00:12:30.560 --> 00:12:32.560
I don't know what is making me repeat it,

00:12:32.560 --> 00:12:34.560
although I don't like the vehicle myself.

00:12:34.560 --> 00:12:35.560
Allahu Akbar.

00:12:35.560 --> 00:12:37.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us goodness,

00:12:37.560 --> 00:12:39.560
a vehicle that will serve its purpose

00:12:39.560 --> 00:12:40.560
rather than a vehicle

00:12:40.560 --> 00:12:42.560
that will bring about arrogance bearing in mind

00:12:42.560 --> 00:12:44.560
that if you have the wealth,

00:12:44.560 --> 00:12:46.560
you are allowed to buy the highest and the best

00:12:46.560 --> 00:12:48.560
of all the vehicles you want

00:12:48.560 --> 00:12:50.560
on condition that it does not make you arrogant.

00:12:50.560 --> 00:12:53.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala bless us.

00:12:53.560 --> 00:12:55.560
So, if we look at them,

00:12:55.560 --> 00:12:56.560
this is what they had.

00:12:56.560 --> 00:12:58.560
Those who had had camels were much more proud

00:12:58.560 --> 00:13:00.560
in terms of the wrong pride

00:13:00.560 --> 00:13:02.560
than those who had had goats and sheep

00:13:02.560 --> 00:13:04.560
who were much more down to earth and humble.

00:13:04.560 --> 00:13:06.560
So much so, subhanallah.

00:13:06.560 --> 00:13:09.560
Allah has kept it such that every nabi,

00:13:09.560 --> 00:13:11.560
every prophet of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:13:11.560 --> 00:13:13.560
He started from a very early age

00:13:13.560 --> 00:13:15.560
looking after goats and sheep.

00:13:15.560 --> 00:13:18.560
Never was it mentioned that they were looking after camels.

00:13:18.560 --> 00:13:19.560
It was always goat and sheep.

00:13:19.560 --> 00:13:21.560
Al-Ghanam, Ra'i Al-Ghanam.

00:13:21.560 --> 00:13:23.560
Ma min nabiyyin illa wa ra'a Al-Ghanam.

00:13:23.560 --> 00:13:25.560
The Prophet salallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:13:25.560 --> 00:13:26.560
there was no prophet,

00:13:26.560 --> 00:13:28.560
except that he started off by looking after sheep.

00:13:28.560 --> 00:13:29.560
By looking after sheep,

00:13:29.560 --> 00:13:31.560
we will get to that inshallah a little bit later.

00:13:31.560 --> 00:13:34.560
So Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala gave them a gift

00:13:34.560 --> 00:13:37.560
by sending them Muhammad salallahu alayhi wa sallam

00:13:37.560 --> 00:13:39.560
to remove them from the darkness of arrogance

00:13:39.560 --> 00:13:41.560
and to make them spend in the cause

00:13:41.560 --> 00:13:42.560
and in the good cause.

00:13:42.560 --> 00:13:44.560
Then another thing they had had

00:13:44.560 --> 00:13:48.560
when it came to their economic life.

00:13:48.560 --> 00:13:50.560
If you take a look at the caravans,

00:13:50.560 --> 00:13:52.560
they had lots of caravans that would travel

00:13:52.560 --> 00:13:55.560
towards the north when it came to the summer

00:13:55.560 --> 00:13:57.560
and towards the south when it came to the winter.

00:13:57.560 --> 00:13:59.560
Because the winters up north were too cold

00:13:59.560 --> 00:14:00.560
for them to handle.

00:14:00.560 --> 00:14:02.560
So they used to go down towards the south,

00:14:02.560 --> 00:14:03.560
towards Yemen.

00:14:03.560 --> 00:14:06.560
And this is why the Quran speaks about these journeys.

00:14:17.560 --> 00:14:21.560
Allah is speaking of the gift of the taming of Quraysh.

00:14:21.560 --> 00:14:23.560
During both of their journeys,

00:14:23.560 --> 00:14:25.560
that which happened in winter

00:14:25.560 --> 00:14:27.560
and that which happened in summer.

00:14:27.560 --> 00:14:29.560
In winter, as I said, they went south

00:14:29.560 --> 00:14:32.560
and in summer they went up towards the north.

00:14:32.560 --> 00:14:35.560
Why does Allah make mention of the taming of Quraysh?

00:14:35.560 --> 00:14:39.560
Because the caravans were waylaid almost all the time.

00:14:39.560 --> 00:14:41.560
They were hijackers and highwaymen

00:14:41.560 --> 00:14:43.560
who came and who would steal and they were wars

00:14:43.560 --> 00:14:45.560
and people used to have to have weapons with them

00:14:45.560 --> 00:14:47.560
in order to fight those

00:14:47.560 --> 00:14:49.560
who want to come and steal and usurp.

00:14:49.560 --> 00:14:51.560
A lot of their economics was based

00:14:51.560 --> 00:14:52.560
on how powerful they were.

00:14:52.560 --> 00:14:54.560
The wars that took place,

00:14:54.560 --> 00:14:56.560
they would usurp and come back.

00:14:56.560 --> 00:14:58.560
If there were some weak tribes,

00:14:58.560 --> 00:15:01.560
they always joined some strong tribes

00:15:01.560 --> 00:15:02.560
and signed treaties with them

00:15:02.560 --> 00:15:05.560
so that they could look after the smaller ones.

00:15:05.560 --> 00:15:07.560
Because the bigger tribes sometimes

00:15:07.560 --> 00:15:09.560
they just went in, usurped and came out.

00:15:09.560 --> 00:15:10.560
Today it happens to us.

00:15:10.560 --> 00:15:12.560
You find someone who is strong and powerful.

00:15:12.560 --> 00:15:14.560
He eats the money of the weak.

00:15:14.560 --> 00:15:15.560
Allahu Akbar.

00:15:15.560 --> 00:15:17.560
And the weak sometimes can do nothing

00:15:17.560 --> 00:15:18.560
unless you know someone.

00:15:18.560 --> 00:15:20.560
When you know someone, they can fix.

00:15:20.560 --> 00:15:22.560
Whoever is trying to fix you.

00:15:22.560 --> 00:15:23.560
That's what has happened today.

00:15:23.560 --> 00:15:25.560
May Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:15:25.560 --> 00:15:27.560
