00:23:58.560 --> 00:24:00.560
Whenever any one of them was informed

00:24:00.560 --> 00:24:01.560
of a female child,

00:24:01.560 --> 00:24:03.560
their faces would be blackened

00:24:03.560 --> 00:24:04.560
and they would become angry.

00:24:04.560 --> 00:24:06.560
They would want to hide behind the walls

00:24:06.560 --> 00:24:08.560
because of the bad news

00:24:08.560 --> 00:24:09.560
that they had just received.

00:24:09.560 --> 00:24:11.560
And they would take the child,

00:24:11.560 --> 00:24:12.560
one of the Sahaba,

00:24:12.560 --> 00:24:13.560
رضي الله عنهم,

00:24:13.560 --> 00:24:14.560
he says,

00:24:14.560 --> 00:24:15.560
in my period of ignorance,

00:24:15.560 --> 00:24:17.560
I buried my daughter,

00:24:17.560 --> 00:24:18.560
she was so beautiful,

00:24:18.560 --> 00:24:19.560
such that she was saying,

00:24:19.560 --> 00:24:20.560
daddy, what are you doing?

00:24:20.560 --> 00:24:21.560
What are you doing?

00:24:21.560 --> 00:24:25.560
And she began to wipe off

00:24:25.560 --> 00:24:27.560
the little sand that was on my beard

00:24:27.560 --> 00:24:28.560
and as she's doing that,

00:24:28.560 --> 00:24:30.560
I kept on putting more and more sand on her

00:24:30.560 --> 00:24:32.560
until she realized what was happening

00:24:32.560 --> 00:24:33.560
and she began to kick

00:24:33.560 --> 00:24:35.560
and then I covered her completely

00:24:35.560 --> 00:24:36.560
and let her die,

00:24:36.560 --> 00:24:37.560
أعوذ بالله.

00:24:37.560 --> 00:24:39.560
So the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم

00:24:39.560 --> 00:24:40.560
asked him,

00:24:40.560 --> 00:24:41.560
this was after Islam,

00:24:41.560 --> 00:24:43.560
didn't you feel in your heart

00:24:43.560 --> 00:24:45.560
a little bit of mercy,

00:24:45.560 --> 00:24:47.560
سبحان الله,

00:24:47.560 --> 00:24:48.560
الله أكبر

00:24:48.560 --> 00:24:50.560
and obviously the heart positively

00:24:50.560 --> 00:24:51.560
felt a lot of mercy,

00:24:51.560 --> 00:24:53.560
but because of the people.

00:24:53.560 --> 00:24:55.560
Sometimes we are embarrassed

00:24:55.560 --> 00:24:57.560
when our own children

00:24:57.560 --> 00:24:58.560
make a little bit of a noise

00:24:58.560 --> 00:25:01.560
and we want to clap them up in public

00:25:01.560 --> 00:25:02.560
just because we want to show the others

00:25:02.560 --> 00:25:03.560
that you know what,

00:25:03.560 --> 00:25:05.560
I'm trying to look after my child,

00:25:05.560 --> 00:25:06.560
that's not the time

00:25:06.560 --> 00:25:07.560
to admonish your child,

00:25:07.560 --> 00:25:09.560
take them home quietly,

00:25:09.560 --> 00:25:10.560
just like how none of us

00:25:10.560 --> 00:25:12.560
would like to be told in public,

00:25:12.560 --> 00:25:14.560
so your children also don't like to be told

00:25:14.560 --> 00:25:16.560
in front of the guests at home

00:25:16.560 --> 00:25:17.560
and it is wrong for you

00:25:17.560 --> 00:25:18.560
to admonish them

00:25:18.560 --> 00:25:19.560
in full view of the public,

00:25:19.560 --> 00:25:22.560
it reduces their confidence levels.

00:25:22.560 --> 00:25:24.560
May Allah سبحانه وتعالى help us,

00:25:24.560 --> 00:25:25.560
may He guide us

00:25:25.560 --> 00:25:27.560
to be true guides to our own children

00:25:27.560 --> 00:25:30.560
although we ourselves need guidance.

00:25:30.560 --> 00:25:33.560
So this was the condition of the people,

00:25:33.560 --> 00:25:34.560
they used to divorce as they wished

00:25:34.560 --> 00:25:36.560
and take back as many times,

00:25:36.560 --> 00:25:38.560
so Allah later on revealed a verse,

00:25:38.560 --> 00:25:41.560
الطلاق مرتان

00:25:41.560 --> 00:25:44.560
فإمساكن بمعروفٍ

00:25:44.560 --> 00:25:49.560
أو تسريح بإحسان

00:25:49.560 --> 00:25:52.560
you can only divorce twice,

00:25:52.560 --> 00:25:54.560
you take back once if you want,

00:25:54.560 --> 00:25:56.560
second time you can take back,

00:25:56.560 --> 00:25:58.560
the minute the third طلاق drops

00:25:58.560 --> 00:25:59.560
or is given,

00:25:59.560 --> 00:26:01.560
you cannot take back until

00:26:01.560 --> 00:26:03.560
and we read these verses this evening

00:26:03.560 --> 00:26:06.560
coincidentally in the surah that we read

00:26:06.560 --> 00:26:08.560
and Allah سبحانه وتعالى says

00:26:08.560 --> 00:26:09.560
until she marries again,

00:26:09.560 --> 00:26:11.560
I need to pause there for a moment,

00:26:11.560 --> 00:26:12.560
why is it the case?

00:26:12.560 --> 00:26:14.560
Most of us don't even know

00:26:14.560 --> 00:26:16.560
how to divorce in Islam

00:26:16.560 --> 00:26:17.560
and people think you just

00:26:17.560 --> 00:26:19.560
dish out three talaqs and walk away,

00:26:19.560 --> 00:26:21.560
never ever do that,

00:26:21.560 --> 00:26:23.560
that is worse than a hooligan,

00:26:23.560 --> 00:26:25.560
worse than an animal,

00:26:25.560 --> 00:26:28.560
it is very sinful to dish out one, two, three,

00:26:28.560 --> 00:26:30.560
very sinful,

00:26:30.560 --> 00:26:31.560
if you would want,

00:26:31.560 --> 00:26:32.560
you need to be calm,

00:26:32.560 --> 00:26:34.560
you need to relax,

00:26:34.560 --> 00:26:36.560
people say I gave my talaq in anger,

00:26:36.560 --> 00:26:37.560
well what do you expect,

00:26:37.560 --> 00:26:39.560
do you think people would now

00:26:39.560 --> 00:26:40.560
be sitting with coffee and say

00:26:40.560 --> 00:26:42.560
my wife I divorce you,

00:26:42.560 --> 00:26:43.560
would that happen?

00:26:43.560 --> 00:26:44.560
Allahu Akbar,

00:26:44.560 --> 00:26:45.560
may Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:26:45.560 --> 00:26:46.560
never make us people

00:26:46.560 --> 00:26:47.560
who are foolish,

00:26:47.560 --> 00:26:48.560
when angry,

00:26:48.560 --> 00:26:50.560
watch your tongue,

00:26:50.560 --> 00:26:51.560
control yourself,

00:26:51.560 --> 00:26:52.560
calm down,

00:26:52.560 --> 00:26:54.560
if you really cannot get along,

00:26:54.560 --> 00:26:55.560
one talaq more than enough,

00:26:55.560 --> 00:26:57.560
you don't need to issue the second,

00:26:57.560 --> 00:26:58.560
you don't,

00:26:58.560 --> 00:26:59.560
not at all,

00:26:59.560 --> 00:27:00.560
may Allah سبحانه وتعالى

00:27:00.560 --> 00:27:01.560
protect us,

00:27:01.560 --> 00:27:02.560
then if you want to get back,

00:27:02.560 --> 00:27:03.560
you can get back,

00:27:03.560 --> 00:27:05.560
no need to marry someone else and so on,

00:27:05.560 --> 00:27:07.560
why is it that the third time

00:27:07.560 --> 00:27:08.560
she cannot get back to you,

00:27:08.560 --> 00:27:10.560
because three whole times

00:27:10.560 --> 00:27:11.560
you tried so hard

00:27:11.560 --> 00:27:13.560
and she couldn't appreciate you

00:27:13.560 --> 00:27:15.560
or you could not appreciate her,

00:27:15.560 --> 00:27:17.560
she will never be able to live with you

00:27:17.560 --> 00:27:19.560
unless she has gone to someone else

00:27:19.560 --> 00:27:21.560
and has had an opportunity

00:27:21.560 --> 00:27:23.560
to compare you with someone else

00:27:23.560 --> 00:27:25.560
to the degree that she could not

00:27:25.560 --> 00:27:26.560
get along with him

00:27:26.560 --> 00:27:27.560
and was divorced from him

00:27:27.560 --> 00:27:28.560
and now she says

00:27:28.560 --> 00:27:29.560
let me go back to that man,

00:27:29.560 --> 00:27:30.560
he was much better,

00:27:30.560 --> 00:27:32.560
there were only 10 things wrong with him,

00:27:32.560 --> 00:27:34.560
this guy there's 100 things wrong with him,

00:27:34.560 --> 00:27:36.560
now there's a chance of it working,

00:27:36.560 --> 00:27:37.560
so this is the logic behind it,

00:27:37.560 --> 00:27:39.560
whereas we think no,

00:27:39.560 --> 00:27:40.560
well you know what,

00:27:40.560 --> 00:27:42.560
there was a man in Britain

00:27:42.560 --> 00:27:43.560
who told me once that

00:27:43.560 --> 00:27:44.560
you know I used to do halalas,

00:27:44.560 --> 00:27:45.560
you know what's a halala,

00:27:45.560 --> 00:27:46.560
for your information,

00:27:46.560 --> 00:27:47.560
it's haram,

00:27:47.560 --> 00:27:49.560
la'anallahu al-muhallil wal-muhallal,

00:27:49.560 --> 00:27:50.560
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:27:50.560 --> 00:27:51.560
has cursed the one

00:27:51.560 --> 00:27:53.560
whom a halala is done for

00:27:53.560 --> 00:27:56.560
and the one who does it,

00:27:56.560 --> 00:27:58.560
where people divorce one, two, three,

00:27:58.560 --> 00:27:59.560
and they have divorced their wives,

00:27:59.560 --> 00:28:00.560
they want to get back,

00:28:00.560 --> 00:28:01.560
so they tell their friends,

00:28:01.560 --> 00:28:02.560
you know what, let's work around this,

00:28:02.560 --> 00:28:03.560
you marry her for one night,

00:28:03.560 --> 00:28:05.560
tomorrow morning you divorce her again,

00:28:05.560 --> 00:28:06.560
when she's finished her iddah

00:28:06.560 --> 00:28:07.560
she'll get back to me,

00:28:07.560 --> 00:28:09.560
so the man says astaghfirullah,

00:28:09.560 --> 00:28:10.560
he says I used to do this,

00:28:10.560 --> 00:28:12.560
and he says until one day,

00:28:12.560 --> 00:28:14.560
oh there was such a princess

00:28:14.560 --> 00:28:15.560
who came in my direction,

00:28:15.560 --> 00:28:17.560
I refused to divorce her,

00:28:17.560 --> 00:28:18.560
he says now she's my wife,

00:28:18.560 --> 00:28:19.560
I've got so many children with her,

00:28:19.560 --> 00:28:20.560
subhanallah,

00:28:20.560 --> 00:28:21.560
Allah protect us,

00:28:21.560 --> 00:28:23.560
yet that is jahiliya,

00:28:23.560 --> 00:28:25.560
Allah curses those who do that,

00:28:25.560 --> 00:28:27.560
why do we not control our tongues,

00:28:27.560 --> 00:28:28.560
for what,

00:28:28.560 --> 00:28:29.560
why do we have to be so foolish

00:28:29.560 --> 00:28:31.560
and then run to the ulama for help

00:28:31.560 --> 00:28:32.560
when we have shot ourselves

00:28:32.560 --> 00:28:34.560
three times in the chest

00:28:34.560 --> 00:28:35.560
with our own gun,

00:28:35.560 --> 00:28:37.560
the bullet piercing straight through the heart

00:28:37.560 --> 00:28:39.560
and we still want to resuscitate,

00:28:39.560 --> 00:28:41.900
the ignorance,

00:28:41.900 --> 00:28:43.900
that was the time of jahiliya,

00:28:43.900 --> 00:28:44.900
before Islam,

00:28:44.900 --> 00:28:45.900
they divorced as they wished,

00:28:45.900 --> 00:28:46.900
took back,

00:28:46.900 --> 00:28:47.900
so the woman was always hanging,

00:28:47.900 --> 00:28:48.900
she didn't know

00:28:48.900 --> 00:28:50.900
whether she was coming or going,

00:28:50.900 --> 00:28:51.900
and then Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:28:51.900 --> 00:28:54.900
blessed them with Muhammad sallallahu alaihi wasallam,

00:28:54.900 --> 00:28:56.900
now if you take a look at some of the good qualities

00:28:56.900 --> 00:28:58.900
that they had had,

00:28:58.900 --> 00:28:59.900
they were very intelligent

00:28:59.900 --> 00:29:01.900
and their memories were very very powerful,

00:29:01.900 --> 00:29:03.900
they could tell you the lineage

00:29:03.900 --> 00:29:05.900
of the camels they had had,

00:29:05.900 --> 00:29:07.900
this camel is the child of this one,

00:29:07.900 --> 00:29:08.900
this one, this one,

00:29:08.900 --> 00:29:09.900
seven generations back,

00:29:09.900 --> 00:29:10.900
today we don't even know

00:29:10.900 --> 00:29:12.900
our own forefathers,

00:29:12.900 --> 00:29:13.900
seven generations back,

00:29:13.900 --> 00:29:14.900
how many of us,

00:29:14.900 --> 00:29:15.900
it's a challenge,

00:29:15.900 --> 00:29:17.900
can mention your father, grandfather,

00:29:17.900 --> 00:29:19.900
great grandfather, great great grandfather,

00:29:19.900 --> 00:29:20.900
going back seven,

00:29:20.900 --> 00:29:21.900
some are saying yes,

00:29:21.900 --> 00:29:23.900
you probably are not from this country originally,

00:29:23.900 --> 00:29:25.900
because with us who are born here,

00:29:25.900 --> 00:29:27.900
we have become very lazy with lineage,

00:29:27.900 --> 00:29:30.900
we barely know the names of our great grandfathers,

00:29:30.900 --> 00:29:32.900
let alone greater than that,

00:29:32.900 --> 00:29:34.900
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us

00:29:34.900 --> 00:29:36.900
the memory of those people

00:29:36.900 --> 00:29:38.900
who knew the lineage of even their animals,

00:29:38.900 --> 00:29:39.900
Subhanallah,

00:29:39.900 --> 00:29:41.900
that's how powerful they were,

00:29:41.900 --> 00:29:42.900
and remember one thing,

00:29:42.900 --> 00:29:43.900
to fulfill,

00:29:43.900 --> 00:29:45.900
this is a very important point,

00:29:45.900 --> 00:29:49.900
to fulfill your duties to your relatives

00:29:49.900 --> 00:29:51.900
is not possible unless you know

00:29:51.900 --> 00:29:52.900
who your relatives are,

00:29:52.900 --> 00:29:55.900
many of us don't even know how we are related,

00:29:55.900 --> 00:29:56.900
Subhanallah,

00:29:56.900 --> 00:29:57.900
and yet we are related,

00:29:57.900 --> 00:29:59.900
then if we take a look,

00:29:59.900 --> 00:30:01.900
they were people who were very honoring

00:30:01.900 --> 00:30:03.900
of the guests in most cases,

00:30:03.900 --> 00:30:04.900
they used to honor their guest,

00:30:04.900 --> 00:30:07.900
you find a person like Hatim al-Ta'i,

00:30:07.900 --> 00:30:08.900
and so many others,

00:30:08.900 --> 00:30:09.900
Abdullah ibn Jad'an,

00:30:09.900 --> 00:30:13.900
he was a very, very generous person,

00:30:13.900 --> 00:30:17.900
anyone came with any story

00:30:17.900 --> 00:30:19.900
of how they were in debt and so on,

00:30:19.900 --> 00:30:20.900
he would sort it out for them,

00:30:20.900 --> 00:30:21.900
he was a poor man,

00:30:21.900 --> 00:30:23.900
and one day he found a lot of wealth,

00:30:23.900 --> 00:30:24.900
and he kept it,

00:30:24.900 --> 00:30:26.900
and he went to one of the elders and said,

00:30:26.900 --> 00:30:27.900
I found a lot of wealth,

00:30:27.900 --> 00:30:28.900
what should I do?

00:30:28.900 --> 00:30:29.900
He says, well,

00:30:29.900 --> 00:30:31.900
you rather help people because that will result

00:30:31.900 --> 00:30:33.900
in you being remembered after you die,

00:30:33.900 --> 00:30:35.900
so he started helping everyone with wealth,

00:30:35.900 --> 00:30:36.900
he was known as very honoring,

00:30:36.900 --> 00:30:38.900
you see people of that time,

00:30:38.900 --> 00:30:39.900
when a guest came,

00:30:39.900 --> 00:30:40.900
they said, yes, yes, come home,

00:30:40.900 --> 00:30:41.900
you have a meal,

00:30:41.900 --> 00:30:42.900
and what they would do,

00:30:42.900 --> 00:30:44.900
they would slaughter their animals,

00:30:44.900 --> 00:30:47.900
...

00:30:47.900 --> 00:30:49.900
How can you ask me about food in my home

00:30:49.900 --> 00:30:50.900
when this camel of mine

00:30:50.900 --> 00:30:51.900
that I'm riding with

00:30:51.900 --> 00:30:52.900
is right in front of you,

00:30:52.900 --> 00:30:53.900
let's cut it out right now,

00:30:53.900 --> 00:30:55.900
and we can enjoy a meal,

00:30:55.900 --> 00:30:58.900
...

00:30:58.900 --> 00:30:59.900
whereas nowadays,

00:30:59.900 --> 00:31:01.900
you try to call a man,

00:31:01.900 --> 00:31:02.900
he doesn't even answer your call,

00:31:02.900 --> 00:31:03.900
why?

00:31:03.900 --> 00:31:04.900
Perhaps he owes you money,

00:31:04.900 --> 00:31:05.900
Allahu Akbar,

00:31:05.900 --> 00:31:06.900
it happens,

00:31:06.900 --> 00:31:08.900
that's when the calls are not answered,

00:31:08.900 --> 00:31:09.900
and then what happens,

00:31:09.900 --> 00:31:10.900
people coming home,

00:31:10.900 --> 00:31:11.900
Alhamdulillah,

00:31:11.900 --> 00:31:13.900
it happens sometimes because

00:31:13.900 --> 00:31:15.900
of the different situations

00:31:15.900 --> 00:31:16.900
that people are in,

00:31:16.900 --> 00:31:17.900
and people say,

00:31:17.900 --> 00:31:18.900
okay, you know what,

00:31:18.900 --> 00:31:19.900
I'll let you know tomorrow,

00:31:19.900 --> 00:31:20.900
that means it's not coming,

00:31:20.900 --> 00:31:21.900
don't worry,

00:31:21.900 --> 00:31:22.900
let you know tomorrow means

00:31:22.900 --> 00:31:23.900
it's not coming,

00:31:23.900 --> 00:31:25.900
so those people had good habits

00:31:25.900 --> 00:31:27.900
which we need to learn from,

00:31:27.900 --> 00:31:29.900
they were honoring of their guests,

00:31:29.900 --> 00:31:30.900
very generous people also,

00:31:30.900 --> 00:31:32.900
they also had generosity,

00:31:32.900 --> 00:31:34.900
then they were very, very courageous,

00:31:34.900 --> 00:31:35.900
that was something else,

00:31:35.900 --> 00:31:37.900
they would go out with all valor,

00:31:37.900 --> 00:31:39.900
they would fight in the cause

00:31:39.900 --> 00:31:40.900
of protecting their own people

00:31:40.900 --> 00:31:41.900
and their tribes,

00:31:41.900 --> 00:31:42.900
they had lots of courage,

00:31:42.900 --> 00:31:47.900
if their fathers or relatives died in battle,

00:31:47.900 --> 00:31:50.900
they were very, very proud of the fact

00:31:50.900 --> 00:31:51.900
that this person died

00:31:51.900 --> 00:31:53.900
whilst protecting this tribe of ours,

00:31:53.900 --> 00:31:54.900
or the clan,

00:31:54.900 --> 00:31:56.900
or the city and so on,

00:31:56.900 --> 00:31:57.900
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:31:57.900 --> 00:31:59.900
grant us some form of courage,

00:31:59.900 --> 00:32:00.900
some of us,

00:32:00.900 --> 00:32:01.900
do not even have courage

00:32:01.900 --> 00:32:02.900
to kill a fly,

00:32:02.900 --> 00:32:04.900
let alone to protect ourselves

00:32:04.900 --> 00:32:05.900
or our family members,

00:32:05.900 --> 00:32:07.900
someone walks over your wife

00:32:07.900 --> 00:32:08.900
or your children

00:32:08.900 --> 00:32:10.900
and swears them in front of you,

00:32:10.900 --> 00:32:11.900
and you can't even say,

00:32:11.900 --> 00:32:12.900
look, please,

00:32:12.900 --> 00:32:13.900
can you understand,

00:32:13.900 --> 00:32:14.900
do not do this,

00:32:14.900 --> 00:32:15.900
sometimes we're just silent,

00:32:15.900 --> 00:32:16.900
we watch oppression

00:32:16.900 --> 00:32:18.900
and we enjoy watching it

00:32:18.900 --> 00:32:19.900
to the degree

00:32:19.900 --> 00:32:20.900
that we are silent

00:32:20.900 --> 00:32:21.900
and we prod it,

00:32:21.900 --> 00:32:22.900
you see,

00:32:22.900 --> 00:32:23.900
if you don't stop oppression,

00:32:23.900 --> 00:32:24.900
the first time it happens,

00:32:24.900 --> 00:32:25.900
it will repeat itself,

00:32:25.900 --> 00:32:27.900
the hadith of the Prophet sallallahu alayhi wa sallam says,

00:32:27.900 --> 00:32:29.900
you must make sure

00:32:29.900 --> 00:32:31.900
that you stop the oppressor,

00:32:31.900 --> 00:32:32.900
if you don't,

00:32:32.900 --> 00:32:33.900
you will begin to make du'a,

00:32:33.900 --> 00:32:34.900
du'a, du'a

00:32:34.900 --> 00:32:36.900
and Allah will not respond to that du'a

00:32:36.900 --> 00:32:37.900
because you did not help yourself

00:32:37.900 --> 00:32:39.900
by stopping the oppressing people,

00:32:39.900 --> 00:32:40.900
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:32:40.900 --> 00:32:42.900
protect us from oppression

00:32:42.900 --> 00:32:43.900
and may He make us stop

00:32:43.900 --> 00:32:45.900
those who are oppressing others.

00:32:45.900 --> 00:32:48.900
So, another thing that they loved

00:32:48.900 --> 00:32:49.900
was to fulfill a promise,

00:32:49.900 --> 00:32:50.900
when they made a promise,

00:32:50.900 --> 00:32:51.900
they made a promise,

00:32:51.900 --> 00:32:52.900
they made a promise,

00:32:52.900 --> 00:32:53.900
they made a promise,

00:32:53.900 --> 00:32:54.900
they would fulfill a promise,

00:32:54.900 --> 00:32:55.900
when they made a promise,

00:32:55.900 --> 00:32:56.900
they would fulfill it,

00:32:56.900 --> 00:32:57.900
in most cases,

00:32:57.900 --> 00:32:58.900
they were a few examples

00:32:58.900 --> 00:33:00.900
of when they did not do that,

00:33:00.900 --> 00:33:01.900
but the whole community

00:33:01.900 --> 00:33:02.900
would team up against them,

00:33:02.900 --> 00:33:03.900
also,

00:33:03.900 --> 00:33:04.900
they were happy with very little,

00:33:04.900 --> 00:33:05.900
they lived in the heat,

00:33:05.900 --> 00:33:07.900
they were happy with small amounts

00:33:07.900 --> 00:33:08.900
of food and drink

00:33:08.900 --> 00:33:09.900
and they were people

00:33:09.900 --> 00:33:11.900
who were always excited

00:33:11.900 --> 00:33:13.900
and they were always happy people,

00:33:13.900 --> 00:33:15.900
but they worshipped idols

00:33:15.900 --> 00:33:17.900
and Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala

00:33:17.900 --> 00:33:18.900
speaks about how

00:33:18.900 --> 00:33:20.900
these people were also quite strong,

00:33:20.900 --> 00:33:22.900
they had strong bodies

00:33:22.900 --> 00:33:23.900
and they were very muscular,

00:33:23.900 --> 00:33:24.900
and they used to compete

00:33:24.900 --> 00:33:25.900
with one another,

00:33:25.900 --> 00:33:27.900
they used to fight as well,

00:33:27.900 --> 00:33:28.900
and they used to protect

00:33:28.900 --> 00:33:30.900
one another at the same time,

00:33:30.900 --> 00:33:31.900
when I say fighting,

00:33:31.900 --> 00:33:32.900
the fighting was more

00:33:32.900 --> 00:33:33.900
with other clans,

00:33:33.900 --> 00:33:34.900
within themselves,

00:33:34.900 --> 00:33:35.900
they tried their best

00:33:35.900 --> 00:33:37.900
not to allow this unity

00:33:37.900 --> 00:33:39.900
to overtake him.

00:33:39.900 --> 00:33:41.900
And then it's important for us

00:33:41.900 --> 00:33:42.900
to make mention of two

00:33:42.900 --> 00:33:44.900
very, very important incidents

00:33:44.900 --> 00:33:46.900
that occurred just before

00:33:46.900 --> 00:33:49.900
the birth of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:33:49.900 --> 00:33:51.900
one of them was the story of Zamzam,

00:33:51.900 --> 00:33:53.900
very interesting story,

00:33:53.900 --> 00:33:55.900
the grandfather of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:33:55.900 --> 00:33:58.900
his name was Abdul Muttalib,

00:33:58.900 --> 00:33:59.900
this Abdul Muttalib

00:33:59.900 --> 00:34:01.900
was one of the leaders of Quraysh,

00:34:01.900 --> 00:34:02.900
Sayyidul Qawm,

00:34:02.900 --> 00:34:03.900
he was the top of Quraysh,

00:34:03.900 --> 00:34:05.900
and he used to have,

00:34:05.900 --> 00:34:06.900
he was a powerful, beautiful,

00:34:06.900 --> 00:34:08.900
meaning handsome man,

00:34:08.900 --> 00:34:09.900
very strong,

00:34:09.900 --> 00:34:10.900
and people looked at him,

00:34:10.900 --> 00:34:11.900
listened to him,

00:34:11.900 --> 00:34:13.900
he was extremely eloquent as well,

00:34:13.900 --> 00:34:14.900
and his place was right

00:34:14.900 --> 00:34:17.900
in the shade of the Kaaba,

00:34:17.900 --> 00:34:19.900
and he had a special mat

00:34:19.900 --> 00:34:20.900
which they laid for him,

00:34:20.900 --> 00:34:21.900
and he would sit on there,

00:34:21.900 --> 00:34:24.900
nobody would ever dare sit on that mat,

00:34:24.900 --> 00:34:25.900
he would sit on it,

00:34:25.900 --> 00:34:28.900
and he would dish out instructions and so on,

00:34:28.900 --> 00:34:30.900
and he had 11 children,

00:34:30.900 --> 00:34:33.900
Subhanallah, 11 sons,

00:34:33.900 --> 00:34:35.900
and from amongst his sons was also

00:34:35.900 --> 00:34:38.900
Abdullah the father of Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam,

00:34:38.900 --> 00:34:40.900
he had various others,

00:34:40.900 --> 00:34:42.900
and what happened is one day he says

00:34:42.900 --> 00:34:44.900
that I was sleeping in Al-Hijr,

00:34:44.900 --> 00:34:46.900
Al-Hijr is the part of the Kaaba,

00:34:46.900 --> 00:34:48.900
nowadays you find a little crescent

00:34:48.900 --> 00:34:50.900
sort of structure,

00:34:50.900 --> 00:34:52.900
it used to be within the Kaaba

00:34:52.900 --> 00:34:53.900
at a certain stage,

00:34:53.900 --> 00:34:55.900
and when they did not have halal funds

00:34:55.900 --> 00:34:56.900
to actually build it in that shape,

00:34:56.900 --> 00:34:58.900
they left it more or less like a cube,

00:34:58.900 --> 00:34:59.900
and that part,

00:34:59.900 --> 00:35:00.900
although it was in the Kaaba,

00:35:00.900 --> 00:35:01.900
is now out of it,

00:35:01.900 --> 00:35:03.900
so if you are reading Salah in it,

00:35:03.900 --> 00:35:05.900
it's as though you are reading Salah in the Kaaba,

00:35:05.900 --> 00:35:07.900
so this man was resting there,

00:35:07.900 --> 00:35:09.900
and he saw a dream,

00:35:09.900 --> 00:35:11.900
in his dream he was told to dig,

00:35:11.900 --> 00:35:13.900
tayba,

00:35:13.900 --> 00:35:15.900
so he asked what is tayba,

00:35:15.900 --> 00:35:17.900
anyway the dream came to an end,

00:35:17.900 --> 00:35:19.900
the next day he was in the same place,

00:35:19.900 --> 00:35:20.900
he had a dream,

00:35:20.900 --> 00:35:23.900
and he was told to dig barra,

00:35:23.900 --> 00:35:25.900
he asked what is barra,

00:35:25.900 --> 00:35:27.900
and the dream came to an end,

00:35:27.900 --> 00:35:29.900
and the third day he saw a dream,

00:35:29.900 --> 00:35:32.900
and the historians all make mention of this,

00:35:32.900 --> 00:35:35.900
and he was told to dig madmoona,

00:35:35.900 --> 00:35:37.900
and he asked what is that,

00:35:37.900 --> 00:35:38.900
and the dream came to an end,

00:35:38.900 --> 00:35:40.900
the fourth day he saw a dream,

00:35:40.900 --> 00:35:43.900
and he was told to dig zamzam,

00:35:43.900 --> 00:35:45.900
so he asked what is it,

00:35:45.900 --> 00:35:48.900
he was told it is a well that will never deplete,

00:35:48.900 --> 00:35:50.900
everyone can drink from it,

00:35:50.900 --> 00:35:52.900
water will gush from it forever and ever,

00:35:52.900 --> 00:35:53.900
it was there,

00:35:53.900 --> 00:35:57.900
he was basically informed exactly where its spot was,

00:35:57.900 --> 00:35:59.900
and he was told its history,

00:35:59.900 --> 00:36:01.900
and he was told where it was,

00:36:01.900 --> 00:36:02.900
so he got up in the morning,

00:36:02.900 --> 00:36:04.900
he got one of his children al-harith,

00:36:04.900 --> 00:36:06.900
according to one of the narrations,

00:36:06.900 --> 00:36:08.900
and the two of them began to dig,

00:36:08.900 --> 00:36:10.900
and Quraysh was watching,

00:36:10.900 --> 00:36:12.900
Quraysh obviously they all related to one another,

00:36:12.900 --> 00:36:14.900
somehow they have different clans

00:36:14.900 --> 00:36:15.900
depending on the children,

00:36:15.900 --> 00:36:17.900
and the children like we have so many brothers,

00:36:17.900 --> 00:36:20.900
each brother a different clan starts from one,

00:36:20.900 --> 00:36:22.900
so they watched him,

00:36:22.900 --> 00:36:24.900
when he started saying Allahu Akbar,

00:36:24.900 --> 00:36:26.900
imagine these were people of ignorance,

00:36:26.900 --> 00:36:29.900
but they still used terminologies referring to Allah,

00:36:29.900 --> 00:36:31.900
because as I said when they had issues,

00:36:31.900 --> 00:36:33.900
they referred it to Allah again,

00:36:33.900 --> 00:36:35.900
but they used to worship others besides Allah,

00:36:35.900 --> 00:36:37.900
like sometimes what happens in our midst,

00:36:37.900 --> 00:36:38.900
we worship Allah alone,

00:36:38.900 --> 00:36:41.900
but then sometimes we happen to worship this and that,

00:36:41.900 --> 00:36:43.900
and sticks and stones and graves and so on,

00:36:43.900 --> 00:36:45.900
and all this is against the law of Allah,

00:36:45.900 --> 00:36:48.900
the whole reason why Muhammad sallallahu alayhi wasallam

00:36:48.900 --> 00:36:52.900
was sent was to remove mankind from worshiping man

00:36:52.900 --> 00:36:54.900
to worshiping the creator of man,

00:36:54.900 --> 00:36:55.900
Subhanallah,

00:36:55.900 --> 00:36:57.900
so let's not lose focus on this,

00:36:57.900 --> 00:36:58.900
so when he said Allahu Akbar,

00:36:58.900 --> 00:36:59.900
Quraysh came around,

00:36:59.900 --> 00:37:00.900
the people came around,

00:37:00.900 --> 00:37:02.900
they saw yes there is water here,

00:37:02.900 --> 00:37:03.900
they started debating,

00:37:03.900 --> 00:37:05.900
hey this water belongs to our forefather,

00:37:05.900 --> 00:37:06.900
who is your forefather?

00:37:06.900 --> 00:37:10.900
Ismail, alayhi salat wa salam,

00:37:10.900 --> 00:37:12.900
and this water came from that time,

00:37:12.900 --> 00:37:14.900
yes and this water belongs to all of us,

00:37:14.900 --> 00:37:15.900
not to you,

00:37:15.900 --> 00:37:16.900
he said no,

00:37:16.900 --> 00:37:17.900
it was in my dream,

00:37:17.900 --> 00:37:18.900
I was instructed,

00:37:18.900 --> 00:37:19.900
had I not been instructed,

00:37:19.900 --> 00:37:21.900
you would have not known about it,

00:37:21.900 --> 00:37:23.900
so they decided okay,

00:37:23.900 --> 00:37:25.900
let's go to someone who can be a judge between us,

00:37:25.900 --> 00:37:26.900
we don't want to fight amongst us,

00:37:26.900 --> 00:37:29.900
and they decided we will go to someone from Bani Sa'd,

00:37:29.900 --> 00:37:31.900
a little bit further up north,

00:37:31.900 --> 00:37:33.900
close to where Sham is,

00:37:33.900 --> 00:37:35.900
very very far from the Arabian Peninsula,

00:37:35.900 --> 00:37:37.900
so a group of them got together,

00:37:37.900 --> 00:37:38.900
the leaders and they left,

00:37:38.900 --> 00:37:40.900
they had a little bit of food with them,

00:37:40.900 --> 00:37:44.900
and they got to a point where the desert stretched and stretched,

00:37:44.900 --> 00:37:46.900
they ran out of food and ran out of water,

00:37:46.900 --> 00:37:48.900
and now all of them were preparing for death,

00:37:48.900 --> 00:37:51.900
Abdul Muttalib and all his clansmen

00:37:51.900 --> 00:37:53.900
and the others who were debating

00:37:53.900 --> 00:37:55.900
going to this one fortune teller,

00:37:55.900 --> 00:37:58.900
so what had happened is they decided okay,

00:37:58.900 --> 00:37:59.900
it's all over,

00:37:59.900 --> 00:38:00.900
the game is over,

00:38:00.900 --> 00:38:01.900
we cannot go back nor can we go further,

00:38:01.900 --> 00:38:03.900
every one of us is going to die,

00:38:03.900 --> 00:38:04.900
the best and most noble thing to do,

00:38:04.900 --> 00:38:06.900
let's all start digging our graves,

00:38:06.900 --> 00:38:07.900
whilst we have a little bit of energy,

00:38:07.900 --> 00:38:11.900
the one who dies first will be buried by those who are to die later,

00:38:11.900 --> 00:38:13.900
so in that way only one will be left out,

00:38:13.900 --> 00:38:17.900
but even he can go down and really get ready to sleep,

00:38:17.900 --> 00:38:18.900
Allahu Akbar,

00:38:18.900 --> 00:38:19.900
so this was their plan,

00:38:19.900 --> 00:38:20.900
they started digging,

00:38:20.900 --> 00:38:23.900
and as they started digging and preparing for death,

00:38:23.900 --> 00:38:24.900
what happened?

00:38:24.900 --> 00:38:30.280
Abdul Muttalib walked towards his camel,

00:38:30.280 --> 00:38:32.280
and suddenly from its feet,

00:38:32.280 --> 00:38:38.280
water started gushing miraculously from the feet of this animal,

00:38:38.280 --> 00:38:40.280
which belonged to Abdul Muttalib,

00:38:40.280 --> 00:38:43.280
at a distance from where everyone was,

00:38:43.280 --> 00:38:45.280
and immediately they were all shocked,

00:38:45.280 --> 00:38:47.280
this was before Islam,

00:38:47.280 --> 00:38:48.280
and they immediately said,

00:38:48.280 --> 00:38:51.280
this is a sign that your well is the well of Zamzam,

00:38:51.280 --> 00:38:53.280
meaning you will be the leader,

00:38:53.280 --> 00:38:55.280
you will be in charge of that water,

00:38:55.280 --> 00:38:57.280
it's not like he was going to have it for himself,

00:38:57.280 --> 00:39:01.280
everyone was going to be obviously quenched from the water of Zamzam,

00:39:01.280 --> 00:39:05.280
but at the same time who was going to be the leader,

00:39:05.280 --> 00:39:07.280
that was what was being discussed,

00:39:07.280 --> 00:39:09.280
so they immediately acknowledged,

00:39:09.280 --> 00:39:10.280
they drank from the water,

00:39:10.280 --> 00:39:12.280
and they said now let's go back,

00:39:12.280 --> 00:39:13.280
no point to go further,

00:39:13.280 --> 00:39:14.280
they went back,

00:39:14.280 --> 00:39:17.280
and Abdul Muttalib was the one responsible for that water,

00:39:17.280 --> 00:39:18.280
he used to feed,

00:39:18.280 --> 00:39:19.280
he used to give the hajjis water,

00:39:19.280 --> 00:39:22.280
those who used to come for that pagan hajj,

00:39:22.280 --> 00:39:24.280
as we made mention of,

00:39:24.280 --> 00:39:27.280
and everyone drank from that water to this day,

00:39:27.280 --> 00:39:31.280
the water is gushing out of that spot in Makkah al-Mukarramah,

00:39:31.280 --> 00:39:32.280
all of us know that,

00:39:32.280 --> 00:39:34.280
and I think in all our homes,

00:39:34.280 --> 00:39:37.280
we have some of that water known as Zamzam,

00:39:37.280 --> 00:39:40.280
the Prophet صلى الله عليه وسلم later says,

00:39:42.280 --> 00:39:46.280
the water of Zamzam is for whatever intention it is drunk for,

00:39:46.280 --> 00:39:48.280
you want to drink it to be cured,

00:39:48.280 --> 00:39:49.280
you will be cured,

00:39:49.280 --> 00:39:50.280
you want to drink it to pass your exams,

00:39:50.280 --> 00:39:51.280
you will pass your exams,

00:39:51.280 --> 00:39:53.280
you want to drink it for sustenance,

00:39:53.280 --> 00:39:54.280
you will have sustenance,

00:39:54.280 --> 00:39:56.280
you want to drink it for any other reason,

00:39:56.280 --> 00:39:57.280
you will have that inshallah,

00:39:57.280 --> 00:39:59.280
for as long as it's a noble reason,

00:39:59.280 --> 00:40:02.280
and the will of Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala accepts that,

00:40:02.280 --> 00:40:05.280
may Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala grant us a drink from Zamzam,

00:40:05.280 --> 00:40:08.280
and may He make us from those who can constantly have it in our homes,

00:40:08.280 --> 00:40:11.280
for indeed it even protects from the devil.

00:40:11.280 --> 00:40:15.590
So this was the story that was worth mentioning,

00:40:15.590 --> 00:40:16.590
and it was a sign,

00:40:16.590 --> 00:40:20.590
because Abdul Muttalib for your information was already informed

00:40:20.590 --> 00:40:22.590
by certain people,

00:40:22.590 --> 00:40:23.590
one was the King of Yemen,

00:40:23.590 --> 00:40:26.590
one was one of the Jewish people he had known,

00:40:26.590 --> 00:40:28.590
and some of the fortune tellers told him that

00:40:28.590 --> 00:40:31.590
from your lineage something big is going to happen,

00:40:31.590 --> 00:40:34.590
one of your grandchildren is going to be a super leader,

00:40:34.590 --> 00:40:37.590
one of your grandchildren is going to come and change everything happening here,

00:40:37.590 --> 00:40:41.590
and he was told this constantly by various people,

00:40:41.590 --> 00:40:44.590
and this was another sign that he was a chosen man,

00:40:44.590 --> 00:40:47.590
Allah subhanahu wa ta'ala chose him to be the grandfather,

00:40:47.590 --> 00:40:48.590
not only the grandfather,

00:40:48.590 --> 00:40:53.590
he looked after Muhammad salallahu alayhi wasallam later on as we will see.

00:40:53.590 --> 00:40:58.590
So the next story that is very very important and worth mentioning,

00:40:58.590 --> 00:41:04.590
is the story of an Abyssinian man who became the King of Yemen,

00:41:04.590 --> 00:41:06.590
and his name was Abraha,

00:41:06.590 --> 00:41:09.590
and this Abraha he was the King of Yemen,

00:41:09.590 --> 00:41:13.590
and he was a Christian man who had built a church in Yemen,

00:41:13.590 --> 00:41:15.590
and he wanted people to flock there,

00:41:15.590 --> 00:41:16.590
for many reasons,

00:41:16.590 --> 00:41:19.590
to worship there as well as for business purposes,

00:41:19.590 --> 00:41:23.590
and he was told that no we have in Mecca,

00:41:23.590 --> 00:41:26.590
there is this house that everyone goes to,

00:41:26.590 --> 00:41:30.590
and you need to deal with them if you want people to come here,

00:41:30.590 --> 00:41:33.590
that was something that he spoke about,

00:41:33.590 --> 00:41:34.590
or he was told,

00:41:34.590 --> 00:41:36.590
so he said no problem,

00:41:36.590 --> 00:41:38.590
I have one elephant, a big elephant,

00:41:38.590 --> 00:41:39.590
we will take the elephant,

00:41:39.590 --> 00:41:41.590
and we will walk through with our armies,

00:41:41.590 --> 00:41:43.590
and we will continue,

00:41:43.590 --> 00:41:45.590
now obviously there is a narration that says,

00:41:45.590 --> 00:41:49.590
the vast of narration say there was just one main big elephant,

00:41:49.590 --> 00:41:51.590
the rest were normal camels and so on,

00:41:51.590 --> 00:41:53.590
and there are some historians who say no,

00:41:53.590 --> 00:41:55.590
it was a whole army of many elephants,

00:41:55.590 --> 00:41:57.590
but the Quran speaks of one elephant,

00:41:57.590 --> 00:41:59.590
Al-feel meaning one elephant,

00:41:59.590 --> 00:42:01.590
so the people of the elephant,

00:42:01.590 --> 00:42:03.590
big huge elephant,

00:42:03.590 --> 00:42:05.590
and there were armies that came with,

00:42:05.590 --> 00:42:07.590
and they started marching towards Mecca,

00:42:07.590 --> 00:42:10.590
when they were outside somewhere near Taif,

00:42:10.590 --> 00:42:13.590
they sent a messenger to say go and look for the Sayyid,

00:42:13.590 --> 00:42:15.590
the leader of these people and tell them,

00:42:15.590 --> 00:42:16.590
we don't want to fight,

00:42:16.590 --> 00:42:19.590
we are coming destroy the house and we're going back,

00:42:19.590 --> 00:42:22.590
so Abdul Muttalib was the leader,

00:42:22.590 --> 00:42:24.590
he was told this is what the man is coming for,

00:42:24.590 --> 00:42:27.590
he said okay, let him come,

00:42:27.590 --> 00:42:29.590
now imagine I told you moments ago,

00:42:29.590 --> 00:42:31.590
these were courageous people,

00:42:31.590 --> 00:42:35.590
and these people would fight to protect their dignity and so on,

00:42:35.590 --> 00:42:37.590
this man said okay let them come,

00:42:37.590 --> 00:42:38.590
and in the process,

00:42:38.590 --> 00:42:43.590
the army came in and usurped more than 200 camel of Quraysh,

00:42:43.590 --> 00:42:46.590
and Abdul Muttalib told one of these men,

00:42:46.590 --> 00:42:49.590
look you can come and destroy the house,

00:42:49.590 --> 00:42:50.590
no problem,

00:42:50.590 --> 00:42:52.590
but our camels we want them back,

00:42:52.590 --> 00:42:55.590
so the man took him to Abraha,

00:42:55.590 --> 00:42:58.590
and Abdul Muttalib spoke to Abraha and told him,

00:42:58.590 --> 00:43:01.590
I would like my 200 camels,

00:43:01.590 --> 00:43:03.590
so Abraha says when I saw you,

00:43:03.590 --> 00:43:05.590
big, huge, handsome man,

00:43:05.590 --> 00:43:06.590
very eloquent,

00:43:06.590 --> 00:43:07.590
I was very happy,

00:43:07.590 --> 00:43:11.590
I thought this man here is a very honored leader here,

00:43:11.590 --> 00:43:13.590
but now that you're asking a favor,

00:43:13.590 --> 00:43:15.590
you have expressed your foolishness,

00:43:15.590 --> 00:43:18.590
we are coming to destroy your honor here,

00:43:18.590 --> 00:43:20.590
we are coming to destroy the house,

00:43:20.590 --> 00:43:23.590
and you want to ask for your camels which is minor,

00:43:23.590 --> 00:43:24.590
it's a small item,

00:43:24.590 --> 00:43:27.590
so he says the camels belong to us,

00:43:27.590 --> 00:43:29.590
we need them back,

00:43:29.590 --> 00:43:31.590
as for the house,

00:43:31.590 --> 00:43:33.590
it has a lord who will protect it,

00:43:33.590 --> 00:43:34.590
that's it,

00:43:34.590 --> 00:43:35.590
Subhanallah,

00:43:35.590 --> 00:43:37.590
and he walked away,

00:43:37.590 --> 00:43:38.590
he was given the camels,

00:43:38.590 --> 00:43:41.590
and these people started proceeding towards the Kaaba,

00:43:41.590 --> 00:43:45.590
the elephant refused to go further,

00:43:45.590 --> 00:43:46.590
it stopped,

00:43:46.590 --> 00:43:47.590
amazing,

00:43:47.590 --> 00:43:48.590
it stopped,

00:43:48.590 --> 00:43:49.590
and they began to beat it,

00:43:49.590 --> 00:43:50.590
it refused,

00:43:50.590 --> 00:43:51.590
didn't go further,

00:43:51.590 --> 00:43:53.590
when they turned it around,

00:43:53.590 --> 00:43:54.590
and beat it,

00:43:54.590 --> 00:43:55.590
it went running,

00:43:55.590 --> 00:43:56.590
when they stopped it,

00:43:56.590 --> 00:43:57.590
and turned it back around,

00:43:57.590 --> 00:43:58.590
it stopped again,

00:43:58.590 --> 00:43:59.590
Subhanallah,

00:43:59.590 --> 00:44:00.590
who stopped it?

00:44:00.590 --> 00:44:01.590
Allah,

00:44:01.590 --> 00:44:03.590
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:44:03.590 --> 00:44:05.590
and as they progressed,

00:44:05.590 --> 00:44:09.590
the armies began to move towards the Kaaba,

00:44:09.590 --> 00:44:11.590
no sooner did they come closer to it,

00:44:11.590 --> 00:44:16.590
then they noticed birds from nowhere in the skies,

00:44:17.590 --> 00:44:21.590
and these birds had three little pebbles each,

00:44:21.590 --> 00:44:23.590
the size of a pea,

00:44:23.590 --> 00:44:24.590
and even smaller,

00:44:24.590 --> 00:44:25.590
small little pebbles,

00:44:25.590 --> 00:44:26.590
made of clay,

00:44:26.590 --> 00:44:28.590
and from a very high altitude,

00:44:28.590 --> 00:44:31.590
they released these pebbles,

00:44:31.590 --> 00:44:34.590
and the pebbles came down at such force,

00:44:34.590 --> 00:44:35.590
you know today we have,

00:44:35.590 --> 00:44:37.590
we learn about gravity,

00:44:37.590 --> 00:44:38.590
and we learn about Newton,

00:44:38.590 --> 00:44:39.590
and this one and that one,

00:44:39.590 --> 00:44:40.590
Wallahi,

00:44:40.590 --> 00:44:43.590
if you take a look at this explanation of Surat Al-Fil,

00:44:43.590 --> 00:44:46.590
you will come to realize that that altitude,

00:44:46.590 --> 00:44:47.590
when it dropped from there,

00:44:47.590 --> 00:44:48.590
the small pebbles,

00:44:48.590 --> 00:44:50.590
went straight through these men,

00:44:50.590 --> 00:44:52.590
and killed them on the spot,

00:44:52.590 --> 00:44:54.590
and people were just watching,

00:44:54.590 --> 00:44:55.590
Allahu Akbar,

00:44:55.590 --> 00:44:57.590
didn't Abdul Muttalib say,

00:44:57.590 --> 00:44:58.590
that house has a Lord,

00:44:58.590 --> 00:44:59.590
who will protect it,

00:44:59.590 --> 00:45:00.590
to this day,

00:45:00.590 --> 00:45:01.590
you need to remember,

00:45:01.590 --> 00:45:03.590
the Kaaba is protected by Allah,

00:45:03.590 --> 00:45:04.590
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:45:04.590 --> 00:45:05.590
may Allah,

00:45:05.590 --> 00:45:06.590
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:45:06.590 --> 00:45:08.590
who sent those birds,

00:45:08.590 --> 00:45:09.590
protect the Kaaba for us,

00:45:09.590 --> 00:45:10.590
and the Haramain for us,

00:45:10.590 --> 00:45:12.590
and may He make us from those,

00:45:12.590 --> 00:45:13.590
who can continue going there,

00:45:13.590 --> 00:45:15.590
in a manner that we are safe and secure,

00:45:15.590 --> 00:45:17.590
and may we never see days,

00:45:17.590 --> 00:45:19.590
when we are prohibited from going there,

00:45:19.590 --> 00:45:21.590
for whatever reason.

00:45:21.590 --> 00:45:22.590
So Allah,

00:45:22.590 --> 00:45:23.590
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:45:23.590 --> 00:45:24.590
sent this,

00:45:24.590 --> 00:45:25.590
and mention is made of this,

00:45:25.590 --> 00:45:26.590
in Surat Al-Fil,

00:45:26.590 --> 00:45:27.590
and Allah,

00:45:27.590 --> 00:45:28.590
Subhanahu wa ta'ala,

00:45:28.590 --> 00:45:29.590
says,

00:45:29.590 --> 00:45:34.590
أَلَمْ تَرَكَيْفَ فَعَلَ رَبُكَ بِأَصْحَابِ الْفِيلِ

00:45:34.590 --> 00:45:37.590
Did you not see what your Rabb has done,

00:45:37.590 --> 00:45:39.590
to the people of the elephant,

00:45:39.590 --> 00:45:41.590
those who came with the elephant,

00:45:41.590 --> 00:45:43.590
Allah destroyed them,

00:45:43.590 --> 00:45:44.590
and some of them,

00:45:44.590 --> 00:45:47.590
whom these pebbles did not get to,

00:45:47.590 --> 00:45:48.590
they were injured,

00:45:48.590 --> 00:45:49.590
they went back,

00:45:49.590 --> 00:45:51.590
and they were inflicted with disease,

00:45:51.590 --> 00:45:53.590
so much so that Abraha himself,

00:45:53.590 --> 00:45:56.590
his organs began to drop,

00:45:56.590 --> 00:45:58.590
literally his fingers started falling off,

00:45:58.590 --> 00:46:00.590
and everywhere they went,

00:46:00.590 --> 00:46:01.590
as they went back,

00:46:01.590 --> 00:46:02.590
they were heading back,

00:46:02.590 --> 00:46:03.590
and his hand fell off,

00:46:03.590 --> 00:46:05.590
next thing his leg fell off,

00:46:05.590 --> 00:46:06.590
and then he died,

00:46:06.590 --> 00:46:07.590
very bad death.

00:46:07.590 --> 00:46:08.590
So these were two incidents,

00:46:08.590 --> 00:46:09.590
that had happened,

00:46:09.590 --> 00:46:12.590
just before the birth of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم,

00:46:12.590 --> 00:46:15.590
then came the blessed birth,

00:46:15.590 --> 00:46:16.590
after which,

00:46:16.590 --> 00:46:19.590
the whole world changed,

00:46:19.590 --> 00:46:21.590
it changed in a way,

00:46:21.590 --> 00:46:22.590
that up to this day,

00:46:22.590 --> 00:46:24.590
that change is felt,

00:46:24.590 --> 00:46:25.590
and up to the end of time,

00:46:25.590 --> 00:46:26.590
there will be people,

00:46:26.590 --> 00:46:28.590
who will be guided by,

00:46:28.590 --> 00:46:31.590
the word of Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم.

00:46:31.590 --> 00:46:33.590
So if you look at us,

00:46:33.590 --> 00:46:36.590
when we look at Muhammad صلى الله عليه وسلم's life,

00:46:36.590 --> 00:46:37.590
as I said,

00:46:37.590 --> 00:46:39.590
we understand revelation,

00:46:39.590 --> 00:46:41.590
he is the one who brought revelation,

00:46:41.590 --> 00:46:43.590
we need to know who he was,

00:46:43.590 --> 00:46:46.590
and his words are known as hadith,

00:46:46.590 --> 00:46:48.590
we need to know who he was,

00:46:48.590 --> 00:46:51.590
his name was Muhammad ابن عبد الله,

00:46:51.590 --> 00:46:52.590
ابن عبد المطلب,

00:46:52.590 --> 00:46:53.590
ابن هاشم,

00:46:53.590 --> 00:46:55.590
ابن عبد منف,

00:46:55.590 --> 00:46:58.590
so he was from the clan of Banu Hashim,

00:46:58.590 --> 00:47:00.590
who fell under Quraysh,

00:47:00.590 --> 00:47:02.590
so his father's name was Abdullah,

00:47:02.590 --> 00:47:04.590
his grandfather was Abdul Muttalib,

00:47:04.590 --> 00:47:05.590
where was he born?

00:47:05.590 --> 00:47:06.590
He was born in Makkah,

00:47:06.590 --> 00:47:08.590
today if you travel to Makkah,

00:47:08.590 --> 00:47:11.590
